channel.title: mycatalog updates
channel.description: 'My Catalog' uses the IBM Cloud catalog API to retrieve data from the catalog. It attempts to be as accurate as possible. This feed shows additions, updates, removals from the catalog. Use with care. It is a work-in-progress :)

item.title: [updated] watsonx.data intelligence (datacatalog) has removed the plan named standard-v3
[updated] Qiskit Runtime (quantum-computing) has changed the description of the plan named open
item.description: *before*: 10 minutes free time per month on select IBM QPUs. After that limit is met, workloads will be blocked and no additional charges will occur., *after*: Provides ten minutes free runtime per month on select IBM quantum computers. After the limit is met, workloads will be blocked and no additional charges will occur.

item.title: [updated] Qiskit Runtime (quantum-computing) has changed the description of the plan named paygo-standard
item.description: *before*: Heron and Eagle processors. Time limits = program-specific up to 8 hours. Qiskit Runtime Second = time counted to process a job. No charge for job queue time., *after*: Pay for the IBM quantum computer access you use. Billed per second of usage.
